  "text": "Linear focal elastosis (LFE) is a disorder of elastic �bers characterized by palpable, hypertrophic, yellowish, linear striae distributed horizontally over the mid and lower back, thighs, arms and breasts, and an increase in abnormal elastic tissue [119] [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Reports on occurrence show that men are more prone than women. Although the pathogenesis of LFE remains unknown, its association with striae distensae may suggest involvement of a process analogous though not identical to keloidal repair [CITATION_3] .",
